reviews.text:
Great breakfast set. The plates are generous with the quantity of meat and fish. They are bigger than Tsui Wah breakfast and much cheaper! Staff is ok but the old woman manager is not that nice.
We will come back.

I came here three times in a row, April 3,4 & 6, 2018, just because I wanted to try duck drumstick rice in soup as it was my fond lunch choice when I was a dyeing factory worker in 1973.  I did not spot the item on the menu when I ordered a tasteless fried noodles set on April 3. When I tried to order it on April 4, it was not available; and I only succeeded on April 6 - the rice with my nostalgic additives cannot be bad!
easy to get seats there. food quality is satisfactory.
